{[%evp 0,28,20,20,29,5,42,42,46,2,7,2,-9,26,15,10,10,-14,-23,-17,-20,-29,1,7,6,-3,13,4,-6,-7,3]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. h4 {This plan is more dangerous with î ..f3 î  Pg7 included.} c5 $1 {The best move here.} ({Black should definitely avoid the careless} 4... Bg7 $6 {in the view of} 5. h5 $36) 5. cxd5 ({Of course not} 5. dxc5 $2 d4 6. Nb5 e5 7. b4 Nc6 $17 {and Black is much better.}) 5... Nxd5 6. Na4 {This plan become popular after the game Carlsen-Vachier Lagrave.} ({The rest moves are just not so good for White:} 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 Bg7 8. Nf3 Bg4 $15 {[%csl Rh4] It is not clear why White played h2-h4.}) (6. dxc5 Nxc3 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. bxc3 Bg7 $15 {The endgame can be worse only for White.}) 6... Nf6 $5 $146 {An interesting novelty.} ({Less recommendable is} 6... cxd4 $6 7. Qxd4 Nf6 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. Nf3 Nc6 {J. Van Foreest - M. Ragger, Chartres, 2022, White has some pressure after} 10. Bf4 $14) ({But} 6... Nc6 $5 {is possible -} 7. e4 Nf6 8. d5 {with very sharp play}) (6... Bg7 {is one more option in the spirit of the Gruenfeld -} 7. e4 Nf6 $5 8. Nxc5 O-O $44) 7. Nxc5 (7. Nf3 {is just fine for Black after} cxd4 8. Qxd4 Qxd4 9. Nxd4 Bg7 $11) 7... e5 ({Black can also start with} 7... Nc6 8. e3 e5) 8. e3 ({Dubious is} 8. Nf3 exd4 9. Nb3 Nc6 {and after} 10. Nfxd4 $6 Ne4 $1 {[%cal Gf8b4]} 11. a3 Bg7 $15 {White must tread with care.}) (8. Nb3 Nc6 9. e3 {just transposes}) 8... Nc6 9. Nb3 exd4 10. Be2 (10. exd4 $143 $6 Bb4+ 11. Bd2 O-O $15) 10... dxe3 {The simplest.} ({Another possibility is the sharper} 10... Bb4+ 11. Kf1 O-O 12. a3 Be7 13. Nxd4 Nxd4 14. Qxd4 Qxd4 ({Black has definitely a good compensation for the pawn after} 14... Qc7 $44 {as well}) 15. exd4 Bf5 $44) 11. Qxd8+ Nxd8 12. Bxe3 Bg7 13. Nf3 O-O 14. O-O Nc6 $11 {Black does not experience any problems in this endgame.} *

